<DocsLayout title="Installation" description="Set up lean-ctx for Cursor, GitHub Copilot, Claude Code, and Windsurf.">
  <p>
    lean-ctx works with any MCP-compatible editor. Below are setup instructions for each supported tool.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Build lean-ctx</h2>
  <pre><code>git clone https://gitlab.pounce.ch/root/lean-ctx
cd lean-ctx
npm install
npm run build</code></pre>

  <p>Note the absolute path to the <code>dist/index.js</code> file — you'll need it for the editor configuration.</p>

  <h2>Cursor</h2>
  <p>Add to your global MCP config at <code>~/.cursor/mcp.json</code>:</p>

  <pre><code>{`{
  "mcpServers": {
    "lean-ctx": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["/absolute/path/to/lean-ctx/dist/index.js"],
      "env": {
        "LEAN_CTX_ROOT": "/path/to/your/project"
      }
    }
  }
}`}</code></pre>

  <p>
    The <code>LEAN_CTX_ROOT</code> environment variable tells lean-ctx which project directory to
    use for relative file paths and the project tree.
  </p>

  <h3>Optional: Cursor Rule</h3>
  <p>
    Run <code>lean-ctx init</code> in your project to create a Cursor rule that instructs the AI
    to prefer lean-ctx tools over built-in tools:
  </p>
  <pre><code>npx lean-ctx init /path/to/your/project</code></pre>

  <h2>GitHub Copilot</h2>
  <p>Add a <code>.vscode/mcp.json</code> file to your project root:</p>

  <pre><code>{`{
  "servers": {
    "lean-ctx": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["/absolute/path/to/lean-ctx/dist/index.js"],
      "env": {
        "LEAN_CTX_ROOT": "\${workspaceFolder}"
      }
    }
  }
}`}</code></pre>

  <p>Copilot reads <code>.vscode/mcp.json</code> automatically when opening the workspace.</p>

  <h2>Claude Code</h2>
  <p>Register lean-ctx as an MCP server via the Claude Code CLI:</p>
  <pre><code>claude mcp add lean-ctx node /absolute/path/to/lean-ctx/dist/index.js</code></pre>

  <p>
    Set the project root before starting a session:
  </p>
  <pre><code>export LEAN_CTX_ROOT="/path/to/your/project"
claude</code></pre>

  <h2>Windsurf</h2>
  <p>
    Windsurf supports MCP servers through its settings. Add lean-ctx in the MCP configuration
    section with the same <code>command</code>, <code>args</code>, and <code>env</code> as shown
    for Cursor above.
  </p>

  <h2>Verify Installation</h2>
  <p>After configuring your editor:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Restart the editor completely</li>
    <li>Open a project file</li>
    <li>Check that <code>ctx_read</code>, <code>ctx_tree</code>, <code>ctx_shell</code>, <code>ctx_benchmark</code>, and <code>ctx_metrics</code> appear in the available MCP tools</li>
    <li>Run <code>ctx_benchmark</code> on a file to verify token counting works</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Automatic Setup</h2>
  <p>
    The <code>lean-ctx init</code> command can set up everything for you:
  </p>
  <pre><code>node /path/to/lean-ctx/dist/cli.js init /your/project</code></pre>

  <p>This creates:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>lean-ctx.config.json</code> — project-specific configuration</li>
    <li><code>.vscode/mcp.json</code> — Copilot + Cursor MCP config</li>
    <li><code>.cursor/rules/lean-ctx.mdc</code> — Cursor rule to prefer lean-ctx tools</li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
